The paper discusses attacks on machine learning models deployed through public APIs, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the specific problem of model extraction, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The attacks are based on exploiting the features of different model classes, which suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper highlights the need for careful model deployment, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE).
